# Student ERP Backend

A FastAPI-based Student ERP backend with PostgreSQL.

---

## Prerequisites

- **Python 3.12+** installed
- **PostgreSQL 16+** installed and running
- **Git** (to clone the repo)

---

## 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <repo-url>
cd nsApp
```

---

## 2. Create the Database

Open **pgAdmin** or `psql` and create a new database:

```sql
CREATE DATABASE your_database_name;
```

---

## 3. Create `.env` File

Create a file named `.env` in the project root (`nsApp/.env`).

**`.gitignore` already ignores `.env`**, so your secrets stay safe.

Replace all placeholders below:

```env
# ============================================================
# Application
# ============================================================
APP_NAME=Student ERP Backend
APP_VERSION=1.0.0
APP_ENV=development
DEBUG=true

# ============================================================
# Database (PostgreSQL)
# ============================================================
DATABASE_HOST=localhost
DATABASE_PORT=5432
DATABASE_NAME=your_database_name
DATABASE_USER=postgres
DATABASE_PASSWORD=your_postgres_password
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://postgres:your_postgres_password@localhost:5432/your_database_name

# ============================================================
# Auth / JWT
# ============================================================
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key_here_at_least_32_chars
ALGORITHM=HS256
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=60

# ============================================================
# Uploads / Logging
# ============================================================
UPLOAD_DIR=uploads
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# ============================================================
# Email (SMTP)
# ============================================================
SMTP_SERVER=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_EMAIL=your_email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your_gmail_app_password

FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

### What to change in `.env`:

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `DATABASE_NAME` | The name you gave your PostgreSQL database |
| `DATABASE_PASSWORD` | Your PostgreSQL password |
| `DATABASE_URL` | Uses the same password and database name |
| `SECRET_KEY` | Generate via: `python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"` |
| `SMTP_EMAIL` | Your Gmail address for sending emails |
| `SMTP_PASSWORD` | Gmail App Password (generate at https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords) |

---

## 4. Set Up Virtual Environment

```bash
# Windows (PowerShell)
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

# Windows (Command Prompt)
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate

# macOS / Linux
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
```

---

## 5. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## 6. Run Database Migrations

```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

This creates all database tables matching the SQLAlchemy models.

---

## 7. Seed Initial Data (Optional)

```bash
python scripts/seed_accounts.py
```

Creates default admin/teacher/student accounts for testing.

---

## 8. Start the Server

```bash
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
or
uvicorn app.main:app
```

- API: **http://localhost:8000**
- Swagger Docs: **http://localhost:8000/docs**

---

## What `.gitignore` Excludes (Must Be Set Up Manually)

| Ignored Item | How to Set Up |
|---|---|
| `.env` | Create from template above |
| `venv/` | Run `python -m venv venv` |
| `__pycache__/` | Auto-created (no action needed) |
| `uploads/` | Auto-created by the app |
| `logs/` | Auto-created by the app |

---

## Project Structure

```
nsApp/
├── .env                    # Environment variables (CREATE THIS)
├── .gitignore
├── requirements.txt        # Python dependencies
├── alembic.ini             # Alembic configuration
├── alembic/                # Database migration scripts
│   ├── env.py
│   └── versions/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py             # FastAPI entry point
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── config.py       # Reads .env
│   │   └── database.py     # SQLAlchemy engine & session
│   ├── core/               # Enums, exceptions, mixins
│   ├── helpers/            # Code generators
│   ├── model/              # SQLAlchemy models
│   ├── routers/            # API route handlers
│   ├── schemas/            # Pydantic request/response
│   ├── repositories/       # Database query layer
│   └── services/           # Business logic layer
├── scripts/
│   └── seed_accounts.py    # Seed default accounts
└── uploads/                # Uploaded files (auto-created)
```

---

## API Endpoints

| Prefix | Description |
|---|---|
| `/auth` | Login, register, email verification, password reset |
| `/admin` | Admin CRUD |
| `/students` | Student CRUD & attendance |
| `/teachers` | Teacher CRUD |
| `/subjects` | Subject management |
| `/classroom` | Classroom CRUD |
| `/assignments` | Assignments & results |
| `/exams` | Exam management & results |
| `/fees` | Fee management |
| `/timetable` | Class timetable |
| `/chat` | Messaging |
| `/notices` | Notices |
| `/study-materials` | Study materials |
| `/daily-class` | Daily class management |
| `/dashboard` | Dashboard statistics |
| `/promotions` | Student promotion |
| `/student-id-cards` | ID card generation |
| `/attachments` | File uploads |
| `/zoom` | Zoom integration |
| `/ka` | Ka / topics |
| `/search` | Global search |
| `/top-students` | Top performers |

---

## Troubleshooting

### `column users.user_code does not exist`

```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### `No module named 'app'`

Make sure you are in `nsApp/` and venv is activated.

### `OperationalError: connection to server`

Ensure PostgreSQL is running and `.env` credentials are correct.
